						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Īśvara-Bhaṭṭārakar at Tiruttavattuṟai in Iḍaiyāṟṟu-nāḍu by the chief <hi rend="bold">Aḍigaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Kumaraṉ Maṟavaṉ</hi> who deposited the amount with two servants of the temple <hi rend="italic">(paṭṭuḍaiyār).</hi> The record has been assigned to <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa</hi> (M.E.R. for 1929, Part II, para. 28).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
